{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "editor",
    "senderColor": "purple",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "YES difficult, 7/10, here is why",
    "content": "Yes, it would be difficult. 7 out of 10.\n\nHard because: (1) the experiential pacing cannot be rearranged — the argument IS the rhythm, so normal editorial tools are off-limits; (2) five registers coexist and the transitions between them are philosophical arguments, not just style shifts; (3) \"phenomenal X\" compounds are 6-8 syllables in English versus 3 in Chinese, creating density I can only manage, not remove; (4) working-draft roughness must be preserved, forcing me to distinguish intentional roughness from translation artifacts; (5) one essay is natively English with its own voice that must not be harmonized with the translations.\n\nManageable because: the author's thinking is always clear — I never have to guess what is meant. The authorial voice is consistent across registers. The formatting system is reliable. The translator's draft so far is strong.\n\nThe difficulty comes from the work's ambition, not from bad writing. Harder than a standard philosophical monograph, easier than translated poetry."
  }
}
